<item>
            <title>[FLINK-1212] Interpreter directive in shell scripts should be &quot;/usr/bin/env bash&quot; instead of &quot;/bin/bash&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-1212</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are some scripts which interpreter directive are &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;#!/bin/bash&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;. We should use &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;#!/usr/bin/env bash&quot;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
